text: <@U02613K0X|jenny> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/jenny/F04VA5BL2/examplewsmessages.zip|exampleWSMessages.zip> and commented: <@U02618EV1> here are three examples of messages being send over the socket for sandbox. Triples is what we're using for topography and has the normalized x,y values of each point in the sandbox only. Soundbox is what I've posted here before; it has the min and max data for each quadrant. Matrix is just a 2d array where the indices represent the position in the frame and the value is the raw depth value. This is currently used for debugging and is not clipping to the sandbox.
